    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-11-21T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-11-21T11:00:00-05:00" n="481"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d481">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2808: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shaw</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-21T16:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 21, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 21—11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>774. From Ambassador Dawes: Sze confidentially informs me that at this
                    afternoon’s Council meeting he will propose a neutral and <pb facs="0625"
                        n="515" xml:id="pg_515"/> nonpartisan commission. He has attempted to frame
                    this proposition so as to cause no immediate break.</p>
                <p>Referring to my 773, November 21, 3 p.m.,<note n="66" xml:id="d481fn66">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_523">p. 523</ref>.</note>
                    giving Sweetser’s report of the meeting yesterday, I have not made any
                    commitments concerning American membership on any body to be appointed and have
                    said that the United States would make a decision in this connection when the
                    occasion so required. [Dawes.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shaw</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
